{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603515","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603515"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:39:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:39:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15764"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15764","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15764"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.54,0,0,0.25,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8455"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71387"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8455","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8455"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15764"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56866"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7080"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20337"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20340"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71387","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71387"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe male pelvic floor contains several important anatomical spaces and pouches.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the lowest point of the male abdominopelvic cavity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rectovesical pouch","Rectovesical septum","Superficial perineal pouch","Deep perineal pouch","Perineum"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Erectovesical pouch\u003C/strong\u003E is the lowest point of the male abdominopelvic cavity. It is formed by the reflection of peritoneum between the rectum and urinary bladder. The \u003Cstrong\u003Erectovesical septum\u003C/strong\u003E is a layer of connective tissue between the rectum and bladder, below the rectovesical pouch.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial perineal pouch\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep perineal pouch\u003C/strong\u003E are spaces inferior to the pelvic diaphragm, containing the superficial perineal muscles and deep perineal muscles respectively. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eperineum\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the external surface area between the pubic symphysis and coccyx, bounded laterally by the ischial tuberosities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The rectovesical pouch is formed by the reflection of peritoneum between the rectum and bladder.","The male pelvic floor consists of several distinct anatomical compartments arranged in descending order: abdominopelvic cavity, pelvic diaphragm, deep perineal pouch, and superficial perineal pouch."],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Gurung P, Yetiskul E, Jialal I. Physiology, Male Reproductive System. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538429/","Foster RA. Male Genital System. Jubb, Kennedy \u0026 Palmer\u0027s Pathology of Domestic Animals: Volume 3. 2016:465\u2013510.e1. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-7020-5319-1.00016-5. Epub 2016 Mar 18. PMCID: PMC7271154","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56866"}},"question":{"data":{"type":